1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,000
Subtitles by KBS World

2
00:00:05,670 --> 00:00:06,860
What is it?

3
00:00:06,860 --> 00:00:08,960
Let's eat first.

4
00:00:08,960 --> 00:00:10,580
What would you like?

5
00:00:10,580 --> 00:00:13,200
Pick whatever you want.
It's my treat.

6
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:14,490
Do you want some meat?

7
00:00:14,490 --> 00:00:17,910
It's lunch. I want something simple.

8
00:00:17,910 --> 00:00:19,490
I'll get bibimbap.

9
00:00:19,490 --> 00:00:21,870
Get meat. My treat.

10
00:00:21,870 --> 00:00:23,850
You're always working too hard.

11
00:00:23,850 --> 00:00:27,230
Excuse me?
What do you have for meat dishes?

12
00:00:27,230 --> 00:00:28,980
It's okay, mom.

13
00:00:28,980 --> 00:00:31,620
Meat's for dinner with alcohol.

14
00:00:31,620 --> 00:00:33,110
I have to go back to work soon.

15
00:00:33,110 --> 00:00:34,770
I'll just get bibimbap.

16
00:00:34,770 --> 00:00:39,160
My daughter can't enjoy her lunch because of that darn job.

17
00:00:39,160 --> 00:00:43,010
Hello? We'd like two stone pot bibimbap.

18
00:00:43,010 --> 00:00:48,790
Make it extra delicious!
It's for my daughter!

19
00:01:00,680 --> 00:01:03,990
Depression must be going around these days.

20
00:01:03,990 --> 00:01:05,760
Depression?

21
00:01:05,760 --> 00:01:09,260
Lots of people die from it.

22
00:01:09,260 --> 00:01:11,680
I'm afraid to watch the news these days.

23
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:16,230
It's filled with stories about people who kill themselves of depression.

24
00:01:17,300 --> 00:01:19,510
But that could happen to us.

25
00:01:20,140 --> 00:01:21,630
But why kill yourself?

26
00:01:21,630 --> 00:01:24,770
You should go on living, no matter what.

27
00:01:25,540 --> 00:01:28,290
It must be unbearable for them.

28
00:01:31,060 --> 00:01:33,280
Your sister might make the news, too.

29
00:01:33,280 --> 00:01:35,550
Let's help her out just this once.

30
00:01:35,550 --> 00:01:37,200
She wants to die.

31
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:41,200
It doesn't take much for someone to go mad.

32
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:47,020
She was sobbing, saying she just wants to die.

33
00:01:47,950 --> 00:01:52,750
I never ever seen her look that lost.

34
00:01:53,390 --> 00:01:56,220
What if she does something stupid?

35
00:01:57,820 --> 00:02:02,620
Minjung wants her to go live with his dad,

36
00:02:02,620 --> 00:02:05,440
but I can't send her when she's depressed.

37
00:02:05,440 --> 00:02:08,960
We should help her find a place in Seoul.

38
00:02:10,040 --> 00:02:11,900
You have money, don't you?

39
00:02:13,410 --> 00:02:16,120
What money?

40
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:19,010
What do you mean, what money?

41
00:02:19,010 --> 00:02:21,800
You've been saving up, I know.

42
00:02:21,800 --> 00:02:23,710
Let's lend Subak that money.

43
00:02:24,750 --> 00:02:29,670
I don't have money. I don't.

44
00:02:29,670 --> 00:02:33,110
But you've been working for years!

45
00:02:33,110 --> 00:02:35,300
I'm not asking it for free.

46
00:02:35,300 --> 00:02:36,880
And it's not for a stranger.

47
00:02:36,880 --> 00:02:39,100
Let's help your sister out.

48
00:02:39,790 --> 00:02:41,980
I'll pay you good interest.

49
00:02:42,630 --> 00:02:46,260
You can make money and do good.

50
00:02:46,260 --> 00:02:49,140
Your father can't sleep these days.

51
00:02:51,280 --> 00:02:53,570
Subak must move out by the end of this week,

52
00:02:53,570 --> 00:02:55,150
so bring the money tomorrow.

53
00:02:55,950 --> 00:02:57,930
I wonder if we can find a place quickly.

54
00:02:57,930 --> 00:02:59,430
Got it? Let's go.
You're finished, right?

55
00:02:59,430 --> 00:03:00,720
Mom!

56
00:03:01,930 --> 00:03:04,180
I don't have that kind of money.

57
00:03:04,640 --> 00:03:06,820
What did you do with the money you made?

58
00:03:07,660 --> 00:03:09,650
I don't make enough money to save.

59
00:03:09,650 --> 00:03:11,510
Sedal doesn't have a job, so...

60
00:03:11,510 --> 00:03:13,140
I'll pay you back!

61
00:03:13,140 --> 00:03:15,730
You think I won't pay you back?

62
00:03:15,730 --> 00:03:17,870
It's not that.

63
00:03:17,870 --> 00:03:22,910
The fortune teller said that your sister is destined to be rich.

64
00:03:23,670 --> 00:03:25,680
I'll tell her to pay you back.

65
00:03:25,680 --> 00:03:27,970
So lend her the money, just this once.

66
00:03:28,700 --> 00:03:31,300
What's my bill?

67
00:03:38,460 --> 00:03:39,380
Hello.

68
00:03:42,980 --> 00:03:45,630
- Can't catch me!
- Stop right there!

69
00:03:50,350 --> 00:03:52,270
It must be hard for you.

70
00:03:53,050 --> 00:03:56,420
It must be since it's your first time.

71
00:03:56,830 --> 00:03:58,670
Parcel service business is hard.

72
00:03:59,860 --> 00:04:03,430
I don't mind it but I'm worried about Subak.

73
00:04:03,430 --> 00:04:07,970
I'd like for her to remain in Seoul,
but I can't afford it...

74
00:04:10,310 --> 00:04:12,700
Since we must take care of my father,

75
00:04:12,700 --> 00:04:16,300
I'd like her to move in with him...

76
00:04:18,670 --> 00:04:21,770
I know I have no right to say this now,

77
00:04:21,770 --> 00:04:26,720
but I'm worried about him living alone.

78
00:04:28,450 --> 00:04:30,830
I'm sure you are.

79
00:04:30,830 --> 00:04:35,360
Your parents were a loving couple,

80
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:37,360
but now your father's all alone.

81
00:04:38,050 --> 00:04:40,190
And you're the eldest son.

82
00:04:42,150 --> 00:04:43,990
I'm living with my mother,

83
00:04:44,840 --> 00:04:47,040
so I know exactly how you feel.

84
00:04:47,710 --> 00:04:52,600
I'd put it off, so I could take care of him when things were better...

85
00:04:58,070 --> 00:05:00,470
But with everything happening,

86
00:05:00,470 --> 00:05:06,280
I really get why they say you should be good to your parents when you can.

87
00:05:09,940 --> 00:05:13,660
My father's different from other men.

88
00:05:13,660 --> 00:05:15,540
My mother was sick for a long time,

89
00:05:15,540 --> 00:05:18,390
so he can take care of the household.

90
00:05:18,390 --> 00:05:23,260
And he's worked hard all his life and being a farmer,

91
00:05:23,260 --> 00:05:25,260
he won't make Subak work hard.

92
00:05:26,330 --> 00:05:28,560
He'll take care of the girls,

93
00:05:28,560 --> 00:05:31,630
and there's a room at the orchard,

94
00:05:31,630 --> 00:05:34,180
so he can stay there.

95
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:37,590
What about you?

96
00:05:37,590 --> 00:05:41,380
I can stay at the office.

97
00:05:44,540 --> 00:05:49,900
Father, can you talk to Subak?

98
00:05:50,910 --> 00:05:54,220
She won't even give me the chance to talk.

99
00:07:03,220 --> 00:07:05,340
Look, isn't this really cute?

100
00:07:05,940 --> 00:07:07,910
This is for you, Sintong.

101
00:07:07,910 --> 00:07:10,940
And this is for you, Bangtong.

102
00:07:10,940 --> 00:07:13,790
Mom, when are we getting new clothes?

103
00:07:13,790 --> 00:07:15,870
We always get stuff people throw out.

104
00:07:15,870 --> 00:07:17,600
We're not special at all.

105
00:07:17,600 --> 00:07:20,060
Oh, yes you are special.

106
00:07:20,060 --> 00:07:21,380
Just wait.

107
00:07:21,380 --> 00:07:24,670
I'm going to get you your own rooms.

108
00:07:24,670 --> 00:07:25,970
- Really?
- Really?

109
00:07:25,970 --> 00:07:27,220
Of course.

110
00:07:27,220 --> 00:07:28,560
We're going to move to an apartment,

111
00:07:28,560 --> 00:07:32,600
and I'll buy you beds and desks.

112
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:34,900
God, please let us buy our own apartment.

113
00:07:34,900 --> 00:07:35,910
Yes, please!

114
00:07:37,940 --> 00:07:39,260
What's all that?

115
00:07:39,260 --> 00:07:41,300
Mom found these at the donation box.

116
00:07:41,300 --> 00:07:43,300
Why do you keep doing that?

117
00:07:43,300 --> 00:07:46,460
You want your boys to wear trash?

118
00:07:46,460 --> 00:07:47,550
If we wash them,
they'll be as good as new.

119
00:07:47,550 --> 00:07:49,190
And they're brand name clothes, too.

120
00:07:49,820 --> 00:07:51,550
The boys don't mind.

121
00:07:51,550 --> 00:07:53,580
Mom's going to buy an apartment.

122
00:07:53,580 --> 00:07:56,950
You're wearing one too.

123
00:07:56,950 --> 00:07:58,250
This is from the donation box?

124
00:07:58,250 --> 00:08:00,350
- You didn't know?
- Man!

125
00:08:00,350 --> 00:08:01,900
Ugh!

126
00:08:02,290 --> 00:08:03,900
You liked it because it's brand name.

127
00:08:03,900 --> 00:08:05,060
Put that back on!

128
00:08:05,060 --> 00:08:06,750
What if the owner of this shirt sees me wearing this and goes,

129
00:08:06,750 --> 00:08:12,930
"Oh, look at him wearing the shirt I threw out."

130
00:08:12,930 --> 00:08:14,700
Would that make you happy?

131
00:08:14,700 --> 00:08:16,820
You don't respect your husband at all!

132
00:08:17,540 --> 00:08:18,900
I'm going nuts.

133
00:08:20,320 --> 00:08:22,210
Your sons are more mature than you.

134
00:08:22,210 --> 00:08:24,600
Ouch! That hurt!

135
00:08:25,340 --> 00:08:26,740
I don't care about buying an apartment.

136
00:08:26,740 --> 00:08:29,970
I just want good food, nice clothes and lots of time to play video games.

137
00:08:29,970 --> 00:08:31,760
Me too, me too.

138
00:08:31,760 --> 00:08:32,740
You two get out!

139
00:08:32,740 --> 00:08:34,740
Mom, don't mind them.

140
00:08:34,740 --> 00:08:36,600
They're just immature.

141
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:40,450
Oh, Sintong, you're the best.

142
00:08:40,450 --> 00:08:44,090
Nice going.
Your own son says you're immature.

143
00:08:44,090 --> 00:08:46,210
Put your shirt back on.

144
00:08:46,210 --> 00:08:48,000
There's nothing to see.

145
00:08:48,000 --> 00:08:50,980
Nothing?
There's plenty to see.

146
00:08:54,010 --> 00:08:57,540
If you turn around

147
00:08:57,540 --> 00:09:01,120
Would we be able to look into the other's eyes?

148
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:02,550
Bounce...

149
00:09:04,150 --> 00:09:05,430
Mother.

150
00:09:08,990 --> 00:09:10,530
I'm home.

151
00:09:10,530 --> 00:09:11,520
Hi.

152
00:09:12,670 --> 00:09:14,270
Did you have dinner?

153
00:09:15,330 --> 00:09:18,720
I don't have an appetite.
Egh, hyo, hyo, hyo.

154
00:09:22,830 --> 00:09:26,750
She made herself bibimbap in this bowl and ate it all.

155
00:09:26,750 --> 00:09:29,750
You still fall for that after 40 years?

156
00:09:30,570 --> 00:09:33,820
She's yelling at me all day,
but acts all weak when she sees you.

157
00:09:33,820 --> 00:09:35,740
I wonder what kind of illness that is.

158
00:09:35,740 --> 00:09:38,490
Egh, hyo, hyo, hyo.

159
00:09:49,100 --> 00:09:51,850
You have to move out this week?

160
00:09:52,540 --> 00:09:53,990
Yes.

161
00:09:54,710 --> 00:09:56,260
Where will you go?

162
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:59,370
What do you mean by that?

163
00:09:59,370 --> 00:10:01,520
She'll stay in Seoul.

164
00:10:01,520 --> 00:10:04,540
But she can't afford to do that.

165
00:10:04,540 --> 00:10:06,230
I know you're upset.

166
00:10:06,230 --> 00:10:09,340
But Minjung's the one who's most upset.

167
00:10:09,340 --> 00:10:11,940
But Minjung did this to himself.

168
00:10:11,940 --> 00:10:16,700
She's done nothing to deserve this,
so she's the one who's most upset!

169
00:10:16,700 --> 00:10:17,780
Is this a competition?

170
00:10:17,780 --> 00:10:22,010
Get Minjung and find out who's more upset.

171
00:10:22,490 --> 00:10:26,010
A married couple must work together,

172
00:10:26,010 --> 00:10:29,060
especially when things become tough.

173
00:10:29,060 --> 00:10:33,390
You had a good life until now, thanks to Minjung, so you should bear this with him.

174
00:10:35,200 --> 00:10:38,770
What? Why should she have to bear this?

175
00:10:38,770 --> 00:10:40,520
She must.

176
00:10:40,520 --> 00:10:42,770
Your mom and I survived hardships together,

177
00:10:42,770 --> 00:10:46,210
And look, she's the boss of me now.

178
00:10:46,210 --> 00:10:47,700
That's how things go.

179
00:10:47,700 --> 00:10:50,430
Your mom had a very hard life.

180
00:10:50,430 --> 00:10:52,280
At least you know!

181
00:10:52,280 --> 00:10:53,650
She did have a hard life.

182
00:10:53,650 --> 00:11:01,560
She used to live with gold nuggets lying around,
using money as toilet paper,

183
00:11:01,560 --> 00:11:03,790
but her life after marrying you was hard.

184
00:11:03,790 --> 00:11:09,260
It wasn't as hard as yours who got arthritis from playing jacks with gold nuggets.

185
00:11:09,260 --> 00:11:11,230
To be honest, what hardships did you suffer?

186
00:11:11,230 --> 00:11:12,850
Did you have to make money?

187
00:11:12,850 --> 00:11:15,830
Or was I a tough mother in law?

188
00:11:15,830 --> 00:11:17,830
You had a good life.

189
00:11:17,830 --> 00:11:21,730
I made money by raising kids and living with a tight budget.

190
00:11:21,730 --> 00:11:24,670
And as for you, everyone already knows how you treat me.

191
00:11:24,670 --> 00:11:28,960
They know you've been mean to me!

192
00:11:28,960 --> 00:11:30,960
- Mom!
- Why? Am I wrong?

193
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:34,660
I never heard such a thing before.

194
00:11:34,660 --> 00:11:37,130
We always veer off the subject.

195
00:11:37,130 --> 00:11:38,450
I know.

196
00:11:39,700 --> 00:11:42,840
Take the girls to your father in law's.

197
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:44,180
I don't want to.

198
00:11:44,180 --> 00:11:46,710
I'm going to stay in Seoul.

199
00:11:46,710 --> 00:11:47,960
Do as I say.

200
00:11:47,960 --> 00:11:50,730
Why are you trying to force her to go?

201
00:11:50,730 --> 00:11:52,570
What if something happens?

202
00:11:52,570 --> 00:11:54,230
She's suffering from depression!

203
00:11:54,230 --> 00:11:56,460
And how can she take care of an old man?

204
00:11:56,460 --> 00:11:58,790
There's a room at the orchard,

205
00:11:58,790 --> 00:12:01,000
and he can take care of himself.

206
00:12:01,000 --> 00:12:02,770
Subak will have it easy.

207
00:12:03,440 --> 00:12:04,770
It won't be.

208
00:12:04,770 --> 00:12:06,020
Just hold on.

209
00:12:06,020 --> 00:12:08,850
Hold on?
Is there another solution?

210
00:12:08,850 --> 00:12:11,100
Are you getting money from somewhere?

211
00:12:16,590 --> 00:12:18,600
- Size 90, 10.
- 90, 10.

212
00:12:18,600 --> 00:12:20,760
- Size 95, 11.
- 95, 11.

213
00:12:21,410 --> 00:12:23,700
- Size 100, 11.
- 100, 11.

214
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:25,000
Just a sec.

215
00:12:28,980 --> 00:12:29,980
Mom, what is it?

216
00:12:29,980 --> 00:12:31,580
My daughter, where are you?

217
00:12:31,580 --> 00:12:33,820
Why are you working so hard?

218
00:12:33,820 --> 00:12:37,370
Nobody will thank you for that, will they?

219
00:12:38,380 --> 00:12:41,650
Hobak, did you think about it?

220
00:12:41,650 --> 00:12:44,550
Mom, let's talk later.
I'm busy right now.

221
00:12:44,550 --> 00:12:46,020
Okay, okay.

222
00:12:46,020 --> 00:12:49,410
There isn't must time... Bye.

223
00:13:23,880 --> 00:13:25,280
Who are you?

224
00:13:26,860 --> 00:13:28,890
This must be the wrong place.

225
00:13:28,890 --> 00:13:33,240
I'm looking for Sintong and Bangtong...

226
00:13:33,240 --> 00:13:36,250
Oh, it's the apartment across the street.

227
00:13:36,250 --> 00:13:39,380
- Oh, thank you.
- Sure.

228
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:48,830
Sintong, Bangtong.

229
00:13:48,830 --> 00:13:50,670
Oh? Hello.

230
00:13:50,670 --> 00:13:52,490
Oh, incredible.

231
00:13:52,490 --> 00:13:54,760
This is the first time she's come to visit us!

232
00:13:54,760 --> 00:13:57,910
Don't be rude. Please come in.

233
00:13:57,910 --> 00:13:59,490
Your mom's not home yet, is she?

234
00:13:59,490 --> 00:14:02,670
Grandmother brought you snacks.

235
00:14:02,670 --> 00:14:04,140
This is so awkward.

236
00:14:04,140 --> 00:14:05,950
Just let it go.

237
00:14:10,130 --> 00:14:12,360
- Hello.
- You're home?

238
00:14:12,360 --> 00:14:15,990
I'm always in the same place...

239
00:14:15,990 --> 00:14:17,390
How did you find us?

240
00:14:17,390 --> 00:14:18,800
You don't know where we live.

241
00:14:18,800 --> 00:14:22,070
I do! I came to Bangtong's 1st birthday party.

242
00:14:23,230 --> 00:14:25,000
Have fun.

243
00:14:25,000 --> 00:14:26,800
Have fun with whom?

244
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:28,550
Come sit down.
I need to talk to you.

245
00:14:28,550 --> 00:14:30,500
Well, I hear someone calling me.

246
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:32,200
I won't yell at you.

247
00:14:32,200 --> 00:14:33,910
So come and sit down.

248
00:14:33,910 --> 00:14:37,160
It's not that.
Someone's calling me.

249
00:14:37,160 --> 00:14:39,950
See? Did you hear that?
I'm coming!

250
00:14:39,950 --> 00:14:41,440
Okay!

251
00:14:47,130 --> 00:14:48,640
Mom, mom, mom.

252
00:14:48,640 --> 00:14:50,220
- What is it?
- Go over to my place.

253
00:14:50,740 --> 00:14:52,080
Is it a roach again?

254
00:14:52,080 --> 00:14:53,480
It's worse than a roach.

255
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:55,390
Hurry up!

256
00:14:55,820 --> 00:14:59,410
Should we get our grandmother?

257
00:14:59,410 --> 00:15:01,850
She'll be over pretty soon.

258
00:15:01,850 --> 00:15:03,580
Sintong, Bangtong!

259
00:15:03,580 --> 00:15:05,180
See?

260
00:15:07,260 --> 00:15:09,570
What brings you here?

261
00:15:09,570 --> 00:15:12,810
To see my grandchildren, of course.

262
00:15:12,810 --> 00:15:13,980
Hello.

263
00:15:14,840 --> 00:15:16,640
I wouldn't recognize you if I ran into you.

264
00:15:16,640 --> 00:15:18,580
Your face changes every day.

265
00:15:18,580 --> 00:15:22,370
Subak's the same.
It changes every 3 months.

266
00:15:22,370 --> 00:15:25,830
Compared to Subak, I'm nothing.

267
00:15:25,830 --> 00:15:29,310
Grandmother, can we take these to our room?

268
00:15:29,310 --> 00:15:32,030
Sure, sure.
Take them to your room.

