Please check and count each size.

534
00:30:33,450 --> 00:30:34,590
Okay.

535
00:30:38,420 --> 00:30:39,850
Yes, mom. What is it?

536
00:30:39,850 --> 00:30:41,600
I was wondering about what I asked you.

537
00:30:42,830 --> 00:30:44,260
I'll stop by on my way home.

538
00:30:44,990 --> 00:30:46,260
You will?

539
00:30:46,260 --> 00:30:48,840
Oh, is there anything you want to eat?

540
00:30:48,840 --> 00:30:50,140
I'll cook it for you.

541
00:30:50,720 --> 00:30:52,140
Okay.

542
00:31:07,110 --> 00:31:09,580
[Ms. Wang Hobak]

543
00:31:12,470 --> 00:31:15,370
Your father can't sleep these days.

544
00:31:15,370 --> 00:31:18,120
Help your sister out.

545
00:31:25,880 --> 00:31:27,760
Welcome.

546
00:31:37,900 --> 00:31:41,580
Please close out all my savings accounts.

547
00:31:41,580 --> 00:31:43,580
All of them?

548
00:31:49,620 --> 00:31:52,110
You only have a few months left.

549
00:31:52,110 --> 00:31:55,460
You'll lose a bit of interest.
Is it okay?

550
00:31:55,460 --> 00:31:57,460
That's too bad.

551
00:31:57,460 --> 00:31:59,130
I need the money.

552
00:32:00,340 --> 00:32:01,360
Okay.

553
00:32:12,130 --> 00:32:15,740
Oh, Ms. Lee.
Hello.

554
00:32:18,960 --> 00:32:20,560
What?

555
00:32:20,560 --> 00:32:22,230
Bangtong did what?

556
00:32:24,280 --> 00:32:26,530
Oh, no!

557
00:32:26,530 --> 00:32:28,650
I'm so sorry, Ms. Lee.

558
00:32:29,540 --> 00:32:33,030
I'll talk to him and teach him a lesson.

559
00:32:34,380 --> 00:32:37,670
Why? Why did you hit your friend?

560
00:32:39,090 --> 00:32:40,300
He was acting up!

561
00:32:40,300 --> 00:32:41,880
That's not an excuse!

562
00:32:41,880 --> 00:32:44,740
Didn't I tell you to be nice to your friends?

563
00:32:44,740 --> 00:32:46,940
A mean boy like him deserves it.

564
00:32:46,940 --> 00:32:48,280
How dare you!

565
00:32:48,280 --> 00:32:50,530
Roll up your pants!

566
00:32:50,530 --> 00:32:51,780
Hit me! Go ahead!

567
00:32:51,780 --> 00:32:54,680
I still won't regret what I did!

568
00:32:54,680 --> 00:32:55,520
What?

569
00:32:55,520 --> 00:32:58,140
How dare you talk to me like that?

570
00:32:58,140 --> 00:33:00,890
I hate you, mom!
You're mean!

571
00:33:04,800 --> 00:33:08,220
Mom, don't hit Bangtong.

572
00:33:08,220 --> 00:33:09,670
He deserves it!

573
00:33:09,670 --> 00:33:10,850
You! You come here!

574
00:33:10,850 --> 00:33:12,240
He had a good reason.

575
00:33:12,240 --> 00:33:16,170
That boy called him a beggar,
saying he was wearing his old clothes.

576
00:33:18,620 --> 00:33:19,480
What?

577
00:33:19,480 --> 00:33:23,790
When he said we were moving to an apartment,
he called him a liar.

578
00:33:23,790 --> 00:33:26,650
Saying a beggar couldn't move to a new place.

579
00:33:27,240 --> 00:33:30,960
I was going to beat him up tomorrow.

580
00:33:30,960 --> 00:33:32,990
So don't hit Bangtong, mom.

581
00:33:39,240 --> 00:33:40,860
Bangtong, come here.

582
00:33:40,860 --> 00:33:41,930
Mommy!

583
00:33:44,670 --> 00:33:46,840
I'm sorry.

584
00:33:46,840 --> 00:33:48,200
I won't hit you.

585
00:33:49,780 --> 00:33:52,020
It's all my fault.

586
00:34:16,500 --> 00:34:18,800
Why don't you quit your job?

587
00:34:19,770 --> 00:34:21,130
Don't ask me to raise your kids!

588
00:34:21,130 --> 00:34:22,580
Why should I?

589
00:34:22,580 --> 00:34:25,650
When your mother in law won't?

590
00:34:26,790 --> 00:34:30,960
I had to raise all of you and raise your uncle.

591
00:34:30,960 --> 00:34:33,210
So how can you ask me to raise your kids?

592
00:34:33,210 --> 00:34:35,980
It's like asking a man to enlist for military service twice!

593
00:34:35,980 --> 00:34:37,300
Don't you agree?

594
00:34:37,930 --> 00:34:40,110
It'd be a different story if you paid me.

595
00:34:40,110 --> 00:34:42,620
But you won't so I can't do it.

596
00:34:49,370 --> 00:34:50,750
How pretty!

597
00:34:51,210 --> 00:34:53,930
She looks just like you.

598
00:34:54,560 --> 00:34:56,240
Because I love you so much,

599
00:34:56,240 --> 00:34:58,020
I love your baby, too.

600
00:34:58,510 --> 00:35:00,630
Oh, precious thing.

601
00:35:00,630 --> 00:35:02,730
Mom, you'll raise her, won't you?

602
00:35:02,730 --> 00:35:05,080
Of course, I will.

603
00:35:05,080 --> 00:35:07,750
You're just a girl, so you couldn't.

604
00:35:07,750 --> 00:35:10,210
Mom, you're the best.

605
00:35:10,210 --> 00:35:13,580
But don't forget to pay me for that.

606
00:35:13,580 --> 00:35:15,920
Your husband makes a lot of money.

607
00:35:18,470 --> 00:35:21,020
I didn't feel this with my own children,

608
00:35:21,020 --> 00:35:23,250
but she's just precious!

609
00:35:24,670 --> 00:35:26,920
I think it's because she looks like you.

610
00:35:44,850 --> 00:35:47,060
- Grandmother, it's me.
- Hello.

611
00:35:47,060 --> 00:35:48,270
You're here often.

612
00:35:48,270 --> 00:35:49,590
You didn't bring anything again?

613
00:35:50,380 --> 00:35:51,550
I'm sorry, grandmother.

614
00:35:51,550 --> 00:35:53,390
I won't come empty handed again.

615
00:35:53,390 --> 00:35:54,540
I don't believe you.

616
00:35:54,540 --> 00:35:56,480
It'd be too later after I die.

617
00:35:56,480 --> 00:35:58,530
Do it while I'm still breathing.

618
00:35:58,530 --> 00:36:00,460
She has no money!

619
00:36:00,460 --> 00:36:03,920
She makes must enough to feed her kids!

620
00:36:03,920 --> 00:36:05,800
Oh, my daughter, you must be tired.

621
00:36:05,800 --> 00:36:08,210
You could've come tomorrow.

622
00:36:09,650 --> 00:36:11,700
What's gotten into her?
Huh?

623
00:36:11,700 --> 00:36:12,980
Is she on drugs?

624
00:36:12,980 --> 00:36:15,230
I haven't seen her take anything.

625
00:36:15,230 --> 00:36:16,630
Did you eat?

626
00:36:16,630 --> 00:36:19,550
I made some miso soup. Want some?

627
00:36:19,550 --> 00:36:21,580
No, I've already eaten.

628
00:36:23,700 --> 00:36:24,520
Mom.

629
00:36:25,300 --> 00:36:26,220
Yes?

630
00:36:27,320 --> 00:36:29,690
I gave a lot of thought to what you said.

631
00:36:30,800 --> 00:36:31,760
Yes?

632
00:36:35,230 --> 00:36:37,280
But I'm sorry, mom.

633
00:36:37,280 --> 00:36:38,670
I don't think I can.

634
00:36:40,070 --> 00:36:41,070
You can't?

635
00:36:41,740 --> 00:36:42,710
No.

636
00:36:43,830 --> 00:36:44,870
Mom, I'm sorry.

637
00:36:46,690 --> 00:36:48,830
Are you afraid I won't pay you back?

638
00:36:49,630 --> 00:36:51,600
It's not that.

639
00:36:51,600 --> 00:36:53,850
You shouldn't be like this.

640
00:36:53,850 --> 00:36:55,360
Your sister's dying!

641
00:36:55,360 --> 00:36:57,500
How can you be so heartless?

642
00:36:57,500 --> 00:37:00,960
If you can't trust me, sign her apartment contract in your name.

643
00:37:01,690 --> 00:37:03,270
Listen to me.

644
00:37:03,270 --> 00:37:05,410
There's no need.
You said no.

645
00:37:06,880 --> 00:37:09,280
Have I ever asked you for help?

646
00:37:09,280 --> 00:37:12,140
It's only a loan.
I'm not asking you to just give it.

647
00:37:12,140 --> 00:37:15,660
And to be frank, you shouldn't be that way.

648
00:37:15,660 --> 00:37:18,360
Subak's been so kind to you!

649
00:37:18,360 --> 00:37:24,140
She pretended to give you work so she could pay you and gave you bags and clothes.

650
00:37:24,140 --> 00:37:27,580
How can you be so ungrateful?

651
00:37:27,580 --> 00:37:29,760
Even strangers would want to pay her back.

652
00:37:29,760 --> 00:37:32,400
You're so greedy and selfish.

653
00:37:32,400 --> 00:37:33,610
Go home.

654
00:37:35,970 --> 00:37:38,110
- Mom.
- I said go home.

655
00:37:49,500 --> 00:37:51,320
You've been to my place.

656
00:37:52,080 --> 00:37:53,980
That's how I live.

657
00:37:54,760 --> 00:37:59,820
I live in a shabby place,
trying to save every penny.

658
00:37:59,820 --> 00:38:02,060
I didn't tell you to live that way!

659
00:38:02,060 --> 00:38:04,010
You can't blame anyone for that!

660
00:38:04,010 --> 00:38:06,290
You don't spend the money you make.

661
00:38:07,340 --> 00:38:08,740
You're right.

662
00:38:08,740 --> 00:38:10,780
I haven't been spending the money I made,

663
00:38:11,710 --> 00:38:14,000
so I can provide a better life for my kids.

664
00:38:14,820 --> 00:38:18,660
So their friends won't call them beggars.

665
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:21,110
What are you talking about?

666
00:38:21,810 --> 00:38:24,400
Subak's had a good life until now.

667
00:38:25,200 --> 00:38:28,880
I want to live in my own place where my kids have their own rooms.

668
00:38:28,880 --> 00:38:30,240
I deserve that.

669
00:38:31,840 --> 00:38:33,980
I've worked really hard for 15 years.

670
00:38:34,890 --> 00:38:37,140
rain or snow, even if I was sick,

671
00:38:37,910 --> 00:38:40,860
even if my kids were burning up,

672
00:38:41,530 --> 00:38:44,590
I never missed a day of work.

673
00:38:44,590 --> 00:38:47,860
I cried every morning when I went to work,

674
00:38:49,520 --> 00:38:54,470
leaving my little kids behind with someone else.

675
00:38:55,230 --> 00:38:57,970
It's not like you worked to make me money!

676
00:38:58,910 --> 00:39:01,390
I got married with no money.

677
00:39:01,390 --> 00:39:06,390
I saved every penny I could and I made them wear clothes people throw out.

678
00:39:06,390 --> 00:39:07,650
And frankly,

679
00:39:08,310 --> 00:39:15,210
I saved up, getting yelled at for not buying you any gifts and working at Subak's house.

680
00:39:15,820 --> 00:39:17,550
I can't use this money on anyone else.

681
00:39:17,550 --> 00:39:19,520
I'm going to use it on my kids.

682
00:39:20,580 --> 00:39:23,380
Go ahead! Who's holding you back?

683
00:39:25,790 --> 00:39:29,070
People would think I'm trying to steal it.

684
00:39:29,070 --> 00:39:32,660
If I asked to borrow it for myself,
you'd have gone mad.

685
00:39:34,520 --> 00:39:37,760
So mom, don't hate me.

686
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:41,310
And don't be disappointed, either.

687
00:39:41,310 --> 00:39:43,180
I'm your daughter, too.

688
00:39:44,160 --> 00:39:46,050
My daughter my butt.

689
00:39:46,050 --> 00:39:47,650
How can you do this to your own mom?

690
00:39:47,650 --> 00:39:49,650
I can't stand you, so leave!

691
00:39:53,010 --> 00:39:54,520
I'm sorry, mom.

692
00:40:01,050 --> 00:40:02,520
Father.

693
00:40:04,080 --> 00:40:05,420
What's going on?

694
00:40:07,580 --> 00:40:09,090
I said what's going on?

695
00:40:09,090 --> 00:40:10,310
It's none of your business.

696
00:40:11,300 --> 00:40:13,510
Did you ask Hobak for money?

697
00:40:14,280 --> 00:40:19,560
You said you found a way,
and that was robbing her savings?

698
00:40:21,140 --> 00:40:22,610
You heard her.

699
00:40:22,610 --> 00:40:25,220
She won't be robbed.

700
00:40:25,220 --> 00:40:27,320
What's wrong with helping her sister out?

701
00:40:27,320 --> 00:40:29,820
I can't believe how heartless she is.

702
00:40:30,150 --> 00:40:32,360
You're the one who's heartless.

703
00:40:32,360 --> 00:40:34,240
Do you even know Hobak?

704
00:40:34,240 --> 00:40:38,330
I'm asking if you know your own daughter.

705
00:40:38,330 --> 00:40:40,330
Oh, man!

706
00:40:40,330 --> 00:40:43,600
The Korean War was nothing compared to this.

707
00:40:43,600 --> 00:40:45,510
Egh, hyo, hyo, hyo, hyo.

708
00:40:46,200 --> 00:40:48,690
You favored Subak since they were young.

709
00:40:48,690 --> 00:40:50,850
Who favored whom?

710
00:40:50,850 --> 00:40:51,780
You did.

711
00:40:51,780 --> 00:40:54,390
That's because Subak was good to me.

712
00:40:54,390 --> 00:40:57,480
She helped us out whenever she could,

713
00:40:57,480 --> 00:40:59,350
she gives us allowance,

714
00:40:59,350 --> 00:41:00,270
and look.

715
00:41:00,270 --> 00:41:02,870
Subak bought us this fridge.

716
00:41:02,870 --> 00:41:06,870
She bought us the TV and the washing machine.

717
00:41:06,870 --> 00:41:08,870
What did Hobak do for us?

718
00:41:08,870 --> 00:41:11,520
She's never even bought us underwear!

719
00:41:14,500 --> 00:41:16,660
Where are you going?
I'm still angry!

720
00:41:16,660 --> 00:41:18,480
I'm going to buy some underwear!

721
00:41:18,480 --> 00:41:20,600
I'm sick and tired of you and the underwear.

722
00:41:20,600 --> 00:41:22,980
What? You don't have any underwear?

723
00:41:22,980 --> 00:41:24,530
I'll buy you a box full of them.

724
00:41:24,530 --> 00:41:26,850
You can put on two or three pairs at once!

725
00:41:29,210 --> 00:41:31,890
I only say that because I'm upset.

726
00:41:31,890 --> 00:41:34,350
People are all the same.

727
00:41:34,350 --> 00:41:37,490
It's natural for you to love the child who treats you better.

728
00:41:37,490 --> 00:41:42,760
Other moms told me that not all children are the same.

729
00:41:42,760 --> 00:41:44,040
What kind of parents are they?

730
00:41:44,040 --> 00:41:47,320
You should learn to control your emotions.

731
00:41:47,320 --> 00:41:50,920
How can you favor one child over another?

732
00:41:50,920 --> 00:41:55,480
Don't you know that it will all come back to bite you later?

733
00:41:55,480 --> 00:41:56,600
No, I don't.

734
00:41:56,600 --> 00:41:58,390
Well, now you know.

735
00:41:58,390 --> 00:42:00,950
Why do you think I put that up there?

736
00:42:00,950 --> 00:42:04,040
Look. Put yourself in other's shoes.

737
00:42:04,040 --> 00:42:08,510
If you do that, you'll find the answer,
but you never do that!

738
00:42:09,320 --> 00:42:11,650
Look at it whenever you pass by it.

739
00:42:11,650 --> 00:42:13,550
I will, I promise so...

740
00:42:13,550 --> 00:42:15,780
Let's tell Subak to move in with us.

741
00:42:15,780 --> 00:42:18,460
What?

742
00:42:18,460 --> 00:42:22,650
We already have a kangaroo,
and now you want a salmon?

743
00:42:22,650 --> 00:42:26,440
She's physically able and capable!

744
00:42:26,440 --> 00:42:28,040
No way!

745
00:42:34,110 --> 00:42:37,420
We have a kangaroo?
He says we do.

746
00:42:37,420 --> 00:42:38,680
Me.

747
00:42:38,680 --> 00:42:41,270
Why are you a kangaroo?
You're human.

748
00:42:41,270 --> 00:42:42,420
I know.

749
00:42:57,900 --> 00:43:00,880
Mom came to see me at work.

750
00:43:00,880 --> 00:43:02,710
Asking me to lend Subak money.

751
00:43:04,450 --> 00:43:07,430
She's never been there, but she found it.

752
00:43:09,420 --> 00:43:12,190
She even came over to my place with snacks for the boys.

753
00:43:13,400 --> 00:43:15,240
Her smile was so warm.

754
00:43:16,300 --> 00:43:18,160
I don't think I have seen that before.

755
00:43:19,950 --> 00:43:23,540
She held my hand asking,

756
00:43:23,540 --> 00:43:25,380
"Did you eat?"

757
00:43:26,140 --> 00:43:27,650
"Are you hungry?"

758
00:43:28,390 --> 00:43:29,790
"Would you like some meat?"

759
00:43:31,050 --> 00:43:32,840
"My treat."

760
00:43:34,070 --> 00:43:36,080
"My daughter's working so hard."

761
00:43:37,690 --> 00:43:42,010
It's the first time she's ever said such things to me.

762
00:43:45,120 --> 00:43:51,620
She called me "my daughter" for the first time when she asked me for money for Subak.

763
00:43:56,040 --> 00:43:58,900
She's acting like it's her money,

764
00:44:00,580 --> 00:44:03,160
and I thought how could she do this to me?

765
00:44:04,320 --> 00:44:10,770
When I told her I couldn't because I want to let my boys have their own rooms,

766
00:44:11,800 --> 00:44:14,160
her expression changed...

767
00:44:16,970 --> 00:44:18,550
Hobak...

768
00:44:18,550 --> 00:44:20,950
Mom doesn't love me.

769
00:44:22,770 --> 00:44:25,120
I don't know why I feel this way.

770
00:44:26,700 --> 00:44:29,840
I'm married and have two kids of my own,

771
00:44:31,030 --> 00:44:33,260
but I still want mom's love.

772
00:44:35,070 --> 00:44:37,280
I must be immature.

773
00:44:39,050 --> 00:44:43,590
Wanting your parents love is natural.

774
00:44:43,590 --> 00:44:45,490
You're quite amazing.

775
00:44:47,940 --> 00:44:49,170
Why?

776
00:44:49,170 --> 00:44:51,500
If I were you,
I wouldn't even have gone over.

777
00:44:51,500 --> 00:44:53,620
And I'd be jealous of Subak.

778
00:44:53,620 --> 00:44:55,240
Don't you hate mom?

779
00:45:00,410 --> 00:45:01,690
I do.

780
00:45:02,770 --> 00:45:06,120
I don't know why she had me.

781
00:45:07,400 --> 00:45:09,560
You're going to heaven.

782
00:45:12,690 --> 00:45:15,030
I must smell like money.

783
00:45:15,030 --> 00:45:17,820
Everyone's asking me to lend them money.

784
00:45:17,820 --> 00:45:19,680
Who else asked you?

785
00:45:19,680 --> 00:45:21,650
My mother in law.

786
00:45:21,650 --> 00:45:25,040
She treated me to pork belly and asked.

787
00:45:25,040 --> 00:45:28,430
I'm scared of people who want to take me out.

788
00:45:28,430 --> 00:45:30,430
There are some at work, too.

789
00:45:31,180 --> 00:45:34,840
How can they ask me for a loan so easily?

790
00:45:34,840 --> 00:45:37,840
It becomes a habit.
It gets easier, I guess.

791
00:45:37,840 --> 00:45:41,690
You do look kind of loaded.

792
00:45:41,690 --> 00:45:47,160
When you get dressed up, you look like a former announcer with a rich husband.

793
00:45:48,850 --> 00:45:50,640
Announcer? No way.

794
00:45:50,640 --> 00:45:53,020
Your dream was to become an announcer.

795
00:45:53,910 --> 00:45:55,310
It was.

796
00:45:56,780 --> 00:46:00,050
I was going to apply after graduating.

797
00:46:01,300 --> 00:46:03,920
But you had to drop out of college because of Subak.

798
00:46:03,920 --> 00:46:05,910
Still, you're amazing.

799
00:46:05,910 --> 00:46:07,350
You're a manager.

800
00:46:09,540 --> 00:46:10,920
Right.

801
00:46:10,920 --> 00:46:14,040
Men aren't attracted to women who look loaded.

802
00:46:14,040 --> 00:46:17,040
You have to look cheap to attract men.

